{"title_page": "Luke Alvez", "text_new": "{{short description|Fictional television character}}\n{{Infobox character\n| name               = Luke Alvez\n| series             = [[Criminal Minds]]\n| franchise          = \n| image              = Luke Alvez Criminal Minds.png\n| alt                = \n| caption            = [[Adam Rodriguez (actor)|Adam Rodriguez]] as Luke Alvez\n| first_major        = \n| first_minor        = \n| first_issue        = \n| first_date         = \n| last_major         = \n| last_minor         = \n| last_issue         = \n| last_date          = \n| first              = \"[[Criminal Minds (season 12)|The Crimson King]]\"<br>12x01, September 28, 2016\n| last               = \"[[Criminal Minds (season 15)|And in the End]]\"<br>15x10, February  19, 2020\n| creator            = [[Erica Messer]]\n| based_on           = \n| adapted_by         = \n| portrayer          = [[Adam Rodriguez (actor)|Adam Rodriguez]]\n| voice              = \n| full_name          = \n| origin             = \n| home               = \n| color              = #B3001B\n| lbl24              = Seasons\n| nickname           = \u00c1lvez, Newbie (by Garc\u00eda)\n| title              = {{nowrap|FBI [[Behavioral Analysis Unit|BAU]] Supervisory Special Agent}}<br> Former FBI Fugitive Task Force Agent<br>U.S. Army Ranger (discharged)\n| occupation         = [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI Special Agent]]\n| family             = \n* Unnamed mother (status unknown)\n* Unnamed father (status unknown)\n* Unnamed grandmother \n* Lisa Douglas (ex-girlfriend)\n* Penelope Garcia (friend at dinner)\n\n\n}}\n'''Luke Alvez''' is a fictional character on the [[CBS]] crime drama ''[[Criminal Minds]]'', portrayed by [[Adam Rodriguez (actor)|Adam Rodr\u00edguez]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/criminal-minds-adam-rodriguez-as-series-regular/|title=Criminal Minds Adds Adam Rodriguez as Series Regular|last=Eng|first=Joyce|date=June 8, 2016|website=[[TV Guide]]|access-date=March 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tvline.com/2016/08/15/criminal-minds-season-12-photo-adam-rodriguez-luke-alvez/|title=Criminal Minds Recruit Adam Rodriguez Swings Into Action|last=Mitovich|first=Matt Webb|date=August 15, 2016|work=[[TVLine]]|access-date=March 26, 2019|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Background and characterization ==\nAlvez was born in the Bronx, New York.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/criminal-minds-luke-alvez-adam-rodriguez/|title=Criminal Minds: Meet Luke Alvez|last=Eng|first=Joyce|date=September 28, 2016|website=[[TV Guide]]|access-date=March 26, 2019}}</ref> Inspired by his father's military service, he joined the U.S. Army and served as a part of the 75th Rangers Regiment in Iraq, as he told [[Emily Prentiss]] ([[Paget Brewster]]).<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite episode|series=Criminal Minds|date=|airdate=October 12, 2016|episodelink=Criminal Minds (season 12)#ep258|network=CBS|number=3|season=12|serieslink=Criminal Minds|title=Taboo}}</ref> After he was discharged, Alvez joined the FBI and worked in several different divisions before being assigned to its Fugitive Task Force, where he became responsible for capturing fugitives on the run. While training with the Task Force, he studied Calvin Shaw ([[Harold Perrineau]]), a disgraced former FBI agent convicted of murdering his confidential informant.<ref>{{Cite episode|series=Criminal Minds|date=|airdate=March 22, 2017|episodelink=Criminal Minds (season 12)#ep272|network=CBS|number=17|season=12|serieslink=Criminal Minds|title=In The Dark}}</ref> Later, one of Alvez's targets is a man named Daniel Cullen (Kraig Dane), a.k.a. ''\"The Crimson King\"''. During the manhunt, the Fugitive Task Force team can't get a positive identification on Cullen during his crimes, so Alvez's partner Phil Brooks ([[Corey Reynolds]]) goes undercover to lure him out. The operation is a success, and Cullen is recaptured, but not before he tortures Brooks. The incident had traumatized Alvez ever since.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite episode|series=Criminal Minds|date=|airdate=September 28, 2016|episodelink=Criminal Minds (season 12)#ep256|network=CBS|number=1|season=12|serieslink=Criminal Minds|title=The Crimson King}}</ref>\n\nAlvez has a dog named Roxy. Because of the affectionate way he talks about her in the office, [[Penelope Garcia]] ([[Kirsten Vangsness]]) thinks at first she is his human girlfriend.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Character arc ==\nIn the [[Criminal Minds (season 12)|Season 12]] premiere he works with the BAU to catch the \"Crimson King\", one of the escapees who attacked his old partner. The team discovers that the real killer is Peter Lewis ([[Bodhi Elfman]]), aka \"Mr. Scratch\", who taunts the team by turning over the real \"Crimson King\", whom Lewis tortured to the point he no longer remembered who he is. After that Alvez decides to join the BAU full-time.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nFollowing the tragic events of [[Criminal Minds (season 12)|Season's 12]] finale titled \"Red Light\",<ref>{{Cite episode|series=Criminal Minds|date=|airdate=May 10, 2017|episodelink=Criminal Minds (season 12)#ep277|network=CBS|number=22|season=12|serieslink=Criminal Minds|title=Red Light}}</ref> in the [[Criminal Minds (season 13)|Season 13]] premiere titled \"Wheels Up\",<ref>{{Cite episode|series=Criminal Minds|date=|airdate=September 27, 2017|episodelink=Criminal Minds (season 13)#ep278|network=CBS|number=1|season=13|serieslink=Criminal Minds|title=Wheels Up}}</ref> Alvez appears to be the only team member who is unharmed after a car crash Lewis caused. He is also the one who comforts Garcia, as she was the one who discovers that Supervisory Special Agent Stephen Walker ([[Damon Gupton]]). When the team discovers where Lewis is hiding, Alvez, Prentiss, [[Spencer Reid]] ([[Matthew Gray Gubler]]) and [[Matt Simmons (Criminal Minds)|Matt Simmons]] ([[Daniel Henney]]) get to the location first. Alvez chases Lewis to the rooftop of the building, but Lewis falls to his death.\n\nIn the sixth episode of [[Criminal Minds (season 14)|Season 14]], title \"Luke\",<ref>{{Cite episode|series=Criminal Minds|date=|airdate=November 7, 2018|episodelink=Criminal Minds (season 14)#ep305|network=CBS|number=6|season=14|serieslink=Criminal Minds|title=Luke}}</ref> four people living in various cities along the [[East Coast of the United States|East Coast]] are tortured and murdered over a three-day span, and the BAU is called in to connect the spree to a [[Drug Enforcement Administration|DEA]]-[[Federal Police (Mexico)|Federal Police]] manhunt for an infamous Mexican cartel hit man. Alvez becomes emotionally involved in the investigation of the case, because of his time spend as an undercover agent on the DEA a few years before. The case becomes personal when the killer, Jeremy Grant ([[Johnny Messner (actor)|Johnny Messner]]), murders Brooks and goes after his girlfriend Lisa Douglas ([[Daniella Alonso]]). For that reason, Prentiss takes him out of the case and tells him to go home. Alvez ignores Prentiss' orders, however, and helps the BAU team catches Grant.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0735226/?ref_=nv_sr_2 Adam Rodriguez] on [[IMDb]]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0452046/?ref_=tt_ov_inf Criminal Minds] on [[IMDb]]\n* [[List of Criminal Minds characters|Luke Alvez: List of Criminal Minds characters]]\n{{Criminal Minds}}\n\n[[Category:Criminal Minds characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional Federal Bureau of Investigation personnel]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters introduced in 2016]]\n[[Category:Male characters in television]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters from New York City]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Fictional television character}}\n{{Infobox character\n| name               = Luke Alvez\n| series             = [[Criminal Minds]]\n| franchise          = \n| image              = Luke Alvez Criminal Minds.png\n| alt                = \n| caption            = [[Adam Rodri